headline: Capital One Stock Pops. Its Earnings Got a Buyback Boost.
summary: Shares of  Capital One Financial  rose Wednesday after the bank breezed past quarterly earnings expectations and announced up to $16 billion in stock buybacks.  Capital One posted adjusted earnings of $5.95 a share for the third quarter, above analysts’ consensus estimate of $4.49.  Capital One stock climbed 3.2% on Wednesday.
